      • setAssetsToLoad

        public void setAssetsToLoad(com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Array<Loader.Asset> textureRegions,
                   com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Array<Loader.Asset> textures,
                   com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Array<Loader.Asset> sounds,
                   com.badlogic.gdx.utils.Array<Loader.Asset> rpgMaps)
        Sets the assets to load next. It must precede any call to loadAssets().
        Parameters:
        textureRegions - The TextureRegion objects to be loaded, which must be properly mapped in the FileMap class (resourcesToDirectory) and the names must contain the extension. It may be null.
        textures - The Texture objects to be loaded, which must be properly mapped in the FileMap class (resourcesToDirectory) and the names must contain the extension. It may be null.
        sounds - The Sound and Music objects to be loaded, which must be properly mapped in the FileMap class (resourcesToDirectory) and the names must contain the extension. It may be null.
        rpgMaps - The TiledMap objects to be loaded, which must be properly mapped in the FileMap class (resourcesToDirectory) and the names must contain the extension. It may be null.

      • loadAssets

        public void loadAssets()
        Starts loading the assets. Loader#setAssetsToLoad() must be called first.
